  "root_text": {
    "an3.31:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3.31 ",
    "an3.31:0.2": "4. Devadūtavagga ",
    "an3.31:0.3": "Sabrahmakasutta ",
    "an3.31:1.1": "“Sabrahmakāni, bhikkhave, tāni kulāni yesaṁ puttānaṁ mātāpitaro ajjhāgāre pūjitā honti. ",
    "an3.31:1.2": "Sapubbācariyakāni, bhikkhave, tāni kulāni yesaṁ puttānaṁ mātāpitaro ajjhāgāre pūjitā honti. ",
    "an3.31:1.3": "Sāhuneyyāni, bhikkhave, tāni kulāni yesaṁ puttānaṁ mātāpitaro ajjhāgāre pūjitā honti. ",
    "an3.31:1.4": "‘Brahmā’ti, bhikkhave, mātāpitūnaṁ etaṁ adhivacanaṁ. ",
    "an3.31:1.5": "‘Pubbācariyā’ti, bhikkhave, mātāpitūnaṁ etaṁ adhivacanaṁ. ",
    "an3.31:1.6": "‘Āhuneyyā’ti, bhikkhave, mātāpitūnaṁ etaṁ adhivacanaṁ. ",
    "an3.31:1.7": "Taṁ kissa hetu? ",
    "an3.31:1.8": "Bahukārā, bhikkhave, mātāpitaro puttānaṁ, āpādakā posakā, imassa lokassa dassetāroti. ",
    "an3.31:2.1": "Brahmāti mātāpitaro, ",
    "an3.31:2.2": "pubbācariyāti vuccare; ",
    "an3.31:2.3": "Āhuneyyā ca puttānaṁ, ",
    "an3.31:2.4": "pajāya anukampakā. ",
    "an3.31:3.1": "Tasmā hi ne namasseyya, ",
    "an3.31:3.2": "sakkareyya ca paṇḍito; ",
    "an3.31:3.3": "Annena atha pānena, ",
    "an3.31:3.4": "vatthena sayanena ca; ",
    "an3.31:3.5": "Ucchādanena nhāpanena, ",
    "an3.31:3.6": "pādānaṁ dhovanena ca. ",
    "an3.31:4.1": "Tāya naṁ pāricariyāya, ",
    "an3.31:4.2": "mātāpitūsu paṇḍitā; ",
    "an3.31:4.3": "Idheva naṁ pasaṁsanti, ",
    "an3.31:4.4": "pecca sagge pamodatī”ti. ",
    "an3.31:4.5": "Paṭhamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an3.31:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 3.31 ",
    "an3.31:0.2": "4. Messengers of the Gods ",
    "an3.31:0.3": "With Divinity ",
    "an3.31:1.1": "“Mendicants, a family where the children honor their parents in their home is said to live with divinity. ",
    "an3.31:1.2": "A family where the children honor their parents in their home is said to live with the first tutors. ",
    "an3.31:1.3": "A family where the children honor their parents in their home is said to live with those worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods. ",
    "an3.31:1.4": "‘Divinity’ is a term for your parents. ",
    "an3.31:1.5": "‘First tutors’ is a term for your parents. ",
    "an3.31:1.6": "‘Worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods’ is a term for your parents. ",
    "an3.31:1.7": "Why is that? ",
    "an3.31:1.8": "Parents are very helpful to their children, they raise them, nurture them, and show them the world. ",
    "an3.31:2.1": "Parents are said to be ‘divinity’ ",
    "an3.31:2.2": "and ‘first tutors’, it’s said. ",
    "an3.31:2.3": "They’re worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods <j>from their children, ",
    "an3.31:2.4": "for they love their offspring. ",
    "an3.31:3.1": "Therefore an astute person ",
    "an3.31:3.2": "would revere them and honor them ",
    "an3.31:3.3": "with food and drink, ",
    "an3.31:3.4": "clothes and bedding, ",
    "an3.31:3.5": "anointing and bathing, ",
    "an3.31:3.6": "and by washing their feet. ",
    "an3.31:4.1": "Because they look after ",
    "an3.31:4.2": "their parents like this, ",
    "an3.31:4.3": "in this life they’re praised by the astute, ",
    "an3.31:4.4": "and they depart to rejoice in heaven.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "an3.31:3.5": "nhāpanena → nahāpanena (bj) ",
    "an3.31:4.3": "Idheva → idhaceva (bj) ",
    "an3.31:4.4": "sagge pamodatī”ti → sagge ca modatīti (bj) "
  },
